column5: Curious how folks did. We had 3 yaks on the water for a couple of days. Moved lots of fish, caught 5 or 6. Nothing over 40". Weed growth here is very slow, so fish seemed to be cruising off the edges. All the fish were caught on smaller lures, couldn't get much interest on larger presentations.
Almost same here, few small cigars caught.
Thanks for the report.Â  Where is "here" BTW? Sounds like the Kawartha's? Smaller fair this time of year is very typical, match the hatch..lol

Haliburton. Some years opener calls for small, some years they are hitting the big stuff. My issue was lots of hits, not a lot hookups.
